Call me old fashioned, but I really love Old Fashioned's. So when my good friend texted me saying this bar had some of the best Old Fashioned's he'd ever had, I knew I had to make a trip to Park Slope and find out.  As a bar, High Dive checks off all the quintessential necessities that I look for: low light, solid music (often eclectic), a committed and regular crowd, space to move around and a free popcorn popper (!) Having sidled up to the bar, I was given pause in my quest for great Old Fashioned's when I saw the list of beers that they had on tap. Covering the entire gamut from pale ales to hearty stouts, it was everything I could stop from audibleing into a glass of hoppy goodness. Undeterred, I ordered my Old Fashioned (bourbon not whisky) and watched as the bartender got to work. Every step looked to be done with care and the final product showed - a delicious, balanced drink with a fresh orange peel and a chunky ice cube, aka heaven on Earth.
